runs.comm: back of a length just outside off, dabbed into the gully
lovely lofted extra cover drive, super timing, length ball picked up from a foot outside off
back of a length, too wide again though, delicately cut and runs it fine of third man, lovely touch
good length on off stump, blocked in the crease
short but too straight and helped backward of square, decent strike again
good length on off stump, White forward and drops it into midwicket for a sharp single
back of a length just outside off and White plays a majestic back foot drive through the covers, that is gorgeous
similar length but straighter and White punches firmly to mid-on
straighter line and pulled this time, gets it in front of square
pulled again, this time along the floor but wide of deep-square leg so they can get back for two
back foot punch and it comes off a thick outside edge down to third man
gets a short one outside off that he dabs in the air but well short of third man
forward just outside off and ran down to third man, they consider a second but it's not on, Hales in quickly off the rope
a foot wide of off stump and clipped down to third man
tighter line and just blocked coming forward
similar delivery, nudged back up to the bowler
fuller and a full swing of the blade brings four down the ground, beats the dive of mid-on
short, pulled, four more, not a clean strike but enough bat backward of square
back of a length around off stump, dabbed into the covers
straighter line, tucked just wide of the leg side 45 for an easy single
gets the line back on off stump and Finch just blocks
forward on off stump and pressed into the covers
another dot ball, blocked into the covers
tight off stump line and blocked again
short and wide, awful ball somehow ends a dot with a firm cut to point
slower ball on off stump, shame for Dernbach it was a half volley and White drove it pleasantly past his left boot
back of a length on off stump, blocked in the crease
short and wide and this time White goes up and over point
back of a length tight to off stump, just blocked
short and wide, cut hard and gets it wide of third man, four more, four balls of that over were total dirt

full delivery, Finch tries to play to leg and it hurries onto him slightly, struck on the pad and given out lbw! Seemed to strike him relatively high on the pad, but, no, knee roll and it was pretty straight too so a fair call on first look. I think Finch might have been forward, caught on the crease somewhat. But Hawk Eye has the ball going over the top so the batsman a little unlucky
forward, dabbing into the covers, point is up quickly and saves the single
short and pulled, total miscue, off the toe of the bat, it loops into midwicket but lands between two fielders
keeps a little low going through a foot outside off stump as White tried to play back
back of a length and punched to mid-off
length ball at the pads, dabbed into midwicket and they get a quick single
reverse paddle goes to short third man and they race a single
down the track and clipped through midwicket for an easy run
back playing with the turn through square leg
step to leg and punched to extra cover where Bopara gets down and saves very well with a dive

length ball, Maxwell steps inside it and swings into the leg side, Bresnan is out at deep-backward square and takes the catch running to his right. More mindless batting from Maxwell, nowhere near the elevation needed on that stroke and he holes out in the deep
played with the spin into the leg side and finds the gap at square leg
short and pulled out to deep square leg
good length, shapes in a touch, Bailey forward to block up to the bowler
Bailey shuffles across his stumps a little and tucks behind square, long leg races in but can't prevent two
tries the late cut but the length was too full for the stroke and gets a bottom edge on the bounce to slip
little straight and flicked out square on the leg side, it's between fielders so they get two
bumper, well-directed but too high apparently, they're so harsh on the bowler's nowadays
full length just outside off, slogged down the ground, not timed at all but over mid-off for a couple
paddle sweep on the reverse side to short third man
horrible slog to the off side from a terrible position and almost falls over backwards having got an edge up the wicket
steps across to this and tucks through midwicket
back and playing firmly to midwicket
down the ground and finding the stands over long-on with a lovely lofted drive, timed well that, Bailey trying to hit his way back into form perhaps
droped into extra-cover, they take on Bopara who gets there then fumbles when trying to throw and somehow the ball runs away towards long-on and they get back for a second
length ball clipped down to long-on
full length at the stumps, clipped through square leg for an easy single
slower ball back of a length outside off, pulled off a bottom edge through square leg
another slowy, a foot outside off, guided down to third man
length ball that almost scuttles onto White's off stump, he plays at the last moment possible to keep it out with a toe-end
fuller ball, punched out to long-on
short and outside the line of off, White sits back and drops one behind square
good ball from Broad, back of a length and zipping through as Bailey tries a little cross-batted dab from the crease
pulls and gets a top edge this time but Buttler can only glove it over the bar, finger tips on it and the ball runs for four. That'll cheer Broad up no end
fullish, pushed towards mid-off halfway forward, the bat turning in the hands
digs this in at the top of Bailey's block, pulled down, well controlled for a single to deep backward square
length ball on off stump, knocked back to the bowler coming forwards
full and in the slot, creamed over long-on, almighty tap from Bailey, who's dealing in sixes himself now
better length, works this one back down the track
digs this in short, Bailey is quickly on it and swats a floaty pull out towards wide long-on for another boundary
length in the channel, steered sharply to point where it's well stopped
short again, merciless from Bailey, smiting Dernbach into the vacant wide long-on area again, it trundles to the rope
four more, this time an inside out drive! The carnage continues for Dernbach, as he tries for the leg stump yorker, Bailey makes room and spears it wide of mid-off
tossed up and nurdled into the leg side for one
length ball, Bailey goes for the big yahoo and under-edges into a gap behind square
White walks forward on off stump and dabs a single through square - raises the bat for fifty at the 'G in front of his home crowd
hello, it's six o'clock! Again it's Bailey bringing the pain, skipping down the track and depositing the ball hiiiiiiiiiiiiigh over long-on
very full, clipped through midwicket
pushed through on the stumps, comes forward and clips past mid-on for one more
length ball on the stumps, nudged with a close of the bat face through square
touch of width from Bopara and this is glided down to the boundary a third man, a delicate cut - and, in a blink, Bailey has fifty too
punched back to the bowler and dropped! Simple caught-and-bowled chance but Bopara shells it
dances forwards and wallops a length ball down the ground, bit of a swipe and it lands short of long-off
tight line on the stumps, turned to leg
slower ball, I think, White waits and nudges another single through square leg
pushed through flat on off, played back to the bowler
tossed up on middle and leg, White glances it firmly through midwicket and beats the boundary rider
slides to leg, flat and quick again, manages to deflect it to short fine leg
darted in, Bailey makes room and clatters a drive over and wide of mid-off for another boundary. The end is nigh!
full toss, on the stumps and swept behind square, Bailey delivers the final blow as Australia win by eight wickets and take the series, 2-0 up with one to play
